# Eval logs roll over each run; keep results CSVs but skip the master log
# (it's append-only and noisy). Comment this out if you want to track it.
eval/logs.json

# Two KBs live side-by-side: data.mi (the production MI corpus, tracked)
# and data.financebench (regression-eval corpus, dev-only). `data` is a
# symlink that points at one of them; the script `scripts/switch_kb.sh`
# repoints it. Code reads from `data/...` unchanged (symlink resolves
# transparently), avoiding the brittle `mv data data.bak` swap pattern.
#
# What we ignore:
# - `data` — the symlink itself (runtime pointer, not source-of-truth)
# - regenerable artifacts under data.mi/ (vector pkl is ~350 MB,
#   over GitHub's 100 MB hard per-file limit; raw is ~1.3 GB)
# - data.financebench/ entirely — dev/eval-only, regenerable from
#   parse_sec/data or by re-running the FinanceBench pipeline.
data
data.mi/dsrag_store/
data.mi/raw/
data.financebench/

# Chainlit auto-creates language packs on first run; bulk + regenerable.
# We keep .chainlit/config.toml for project-specific overrides.
.chainlit/translations/
